title: Parkland field hockey team holds off Nazareth
text:

Parkland 3, Nazareth 2 -- Rapid Recap 
Parkland High School's field hockey team took a two-goal lead in the first half Tuesday and held on for a 3-2 Eastern Pennsylvania Conference victory over Nazareth . 
Turning point : Grace Royer scored the game's third goal in less than two minutes. It broke a 1-1 tie and put the Trojans ahead to stay. 
Top performers : Royer and Rachel Rizzetto scored within a 13-minute span in the first half as the Trojans pulled away from a 1-1 tie. Jenna Lysakowski scored Parkland's first goal. 
What it means : Parkland wins a hard-fought game on its home field in a battle of evenly matched teams. Both teams need two more victories to qualify for the District 11 Class AAA playoffs.
